    <stitle>FRAME - MXT - FRAME ALIGNMENT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>FRAME ALIGNMENT</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>The frame must be properly aligned as this affects body, axle and suspension mounting. If the vehicle
                has been involved in an accident or has been overloaded, it is recommended that the frame be checked for
                proper alignment.
            </para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="align" graphiccount="0">
            <title>PRE-ALIGNMENT INSPECTION</title>
            <para>Before checking alignment, park vehicle on level ground and set parking brake. Inspect frame assembly
                for loose parts, welds, cracks and bends. Be sure to make all necessary repairs before attempting to
                check frame alignment.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
